
⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 77/120 – struct()

🎤 Interview Question

You are given an employee DataFrame with the columns:

emp_id

name

department


Write PySpark code to combine name and department into a single struct column named employee_info.


---

📊 Input Dataset

emp_id	name	department

101	John	IT
102	Alice	HR



---

✅ Expected Output

emp_id	employee_info

101	{John, IT}
102	{Alice, HR}



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.functions import struct

df.select(
    "emp_id",
    struct("name", "department").alias("employee_info")
).show(truncate=False)


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. What is a Struct in PySpark?

Answer

A StructType groups multiple columns into a single nested column.


---

Q2. Where is struct() commonly used?

Answer

Nested JSON creation

API payload generation

Delta Lake nested schemas

Kafka message construction



---

Q3. How do you access fields inside a struct?

Answer

df.select("employee_info.name")

or

df.select("employee_info.department")


