⭐⭐⭐⭐☆ Question 78/120 – create_map()

🎤 Interview Question

Write PySpark code to create a map where:

Key = department

Value = salary



---

📊 Input Dataset

emp_id	department	salary

101	IT	60000
102	HR	50000



---

✅ Expected Output

emp_id	dept_salary

101	{IT -> 60000}
102	{HR -> 50000}



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.functions import create_map, col

df.select(
    "emp_id",
    create_map(
        col("department"),
        col("salary")
    ).alias("dept_salary")
).show(truncate=False)


---

