⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 80/120 – to_json()

🎤 Interview Question

Convert a struct column into a JSON string.


---

📊 Input Dataset

emp_id	employee_info

101	{John,60000}
102	{Alice,70000}



---

✅ Expected Output

emp_id	employee_json

101	{"name":"John","salary":60000}
102	{"name":"Alice","salary":70000}



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.functions import to_json, struct

df = df.withColumn(
    "employee_json",
    to_json(
        struct("name", "salary")
    )
)

df.show(truncate=False)


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. What does to_json() do?

Answer

It converts a struct, array, or map column into a JSON string.


---

Q2. Where is to_json() commonly used?

Answer

Writing API payloads

Kafka producers

Event publishing

JSON exports



---

Q3. Can to_json() convert arrays and maps?

Answer

Yes. It supports:

StructType

ArrayType

MapType



